comment: These damn scaley directors will be the death of me
Not gonna lie, I honestly asked myself, "I wonder if this is what scalies imagine it to be like?"

You know the world's messed up when it's getting normalised
No joke, I do wonder ow much it will come to be seen as "okay" in the near-ish future by the general populace?
By near-ish, I mean a generation or two.
Considering all the tolerance that's goin' around, it seems inevitable

And, I mean, look at movies like Zootopia and Rock Dog on top of countless tv cartoons starring anthropomophic cast. There's gonna be an entire generation of adults in a few years that grew up with a huge amount of influence.
SJW bullshittery nonwithstanding, I think there's gonna be a weird surge in furries coming up.
Like, are there gonna be cliques at school? Like the goth kids?
Disliked, but more or less tolerated?
I can see it now.... "Excuse me, we're not a clique, we're a Pack!"
Ooo I can picture that clearly
There's always been things that "trigger" furry outbreaks
Zootopia is a whole different scale though, I guess
And the prevalence of availability of the internet and it's weirdness to younger and younger people is gonna have an impact I think.
Like, 20 years ago, if Starfox piqued your interest, you were pretty much stuck with that and whatever other influences were inside your house.
But now, for better or for worse, the entire fandom is just a few google searches away.
Tom didnt even know what furries were when he made twokinds
Now another kid making a webcomic would learn about them instantly
I think I was 15 when I found out from a dude passing out anti-furry propeganda at school. I shit you not.
